      <span class="tick-item">TypeScript</span><span class="tick-item"
        >FastAPI</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">Node.js</span><span class="tick-item"
        >PostgreSQL</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">Docker</span><span class="tick-item">Rust</span>
      <span class="tick-item">Arch Linux</span><span class="tick-item"
        >Nginx</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">Kubernetes</span><span class="tick-item"
        >Prisma</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">TailwindCSS</span><span class="tick-item"
        >Python</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">DWM</span><span class="tick-item">OpenCV</span>
      <span class="tick-item">Next.js</span><span class="tick-item">React</span>
      <span class="tick-item">TypeScript</span><span class="tick-item"
        >FastAPI</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">Node.js</span><span class="tick-item"
        >PostgreSQL</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">Docker</span><span class="tick-item">Rust</span>
      <span class="tick-item">Arch Linux</span><span class="tick-item"
        >Nginx</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">Kubernetes</span><span class="tick-item"
        >Prisma</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">TailwindCSS</span><span class="tick-item"
        >Python</span
      >
      <span class="tick-item">DWM</span><span class="tick-item">OpenCV</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ABOUT STRIP -->
  <div class="about-strip">
    <div class="about-strip-left">
      <div class="section-tag">01 — About</div>
      <h2 class="section-h">
        Minimalism<br />meets<br /><span style="color:var(--red)"
          >Performance.</span
        >
      </h2>
      <p class="section-sub">
        I ship fast, self-host everything, and believe you should own your
        stack.
      </p>
      <div class="ctas">
        <a href="/about" class="btn-primary">More About Me</a>
        <a href="/Resume.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn-outline">Resume ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="about-strip-right">
      <div class="about-prose">
        <p>
          I'm a <strong>Full Stack Engineer</strong> from Mumbai, building production-grade
          systems with Next.js, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, and Docker. My journey started
          with JavaScript — now I'm deep in <strong>Linux internals</strong>,
          K8s in production, and self-hosting everything possible.
        </p>
        <p>
          I run a custom <strong>DWM setup</strong> on Arch Linux, wrote a color picker
          in Rust that's now on the AUR, and believe the best code is the code you
          control — from the metal up.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-terminal">
        <div class="mini-terminal-bar">
          <div class="t-dot t-red"></div>
          <div class="t-dot t-yellow"></div>
          <div class="t-dot t-green"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="mini-terminal-body">
          <div>
            <span class="tc">distro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span
              class="tg">: Arch Linux (btw)</span
            >
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="tc"
              >wm&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="tv">: DWM — riced &amp; suckless</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="tc">learning&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="tv"
              >: Linux internals, K8s in prod</span
            >
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="tc">obsessing </span><span class="tr"
              >: self-hosting everything</span
            >
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="tc">email&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span
              class="tv">: lakhani.siddhesh@gmail.com</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SELECTED WORK -->
  <div class="work-section">
    <div class="work-header">
      <div>
        <div class="section-tag">02 — Work</div>
        <h2 class="section-h">Selected<br />Projects.</h2>
      </div>
      <a href="/projects" class="btn-outline">All Projects →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="work-grid">
      <a href="/projects" class="wcard featured">
        <span class="wcard-arrow">↗</span>
        <div class="wcard-num">Featured</div>
        <h3 class="wcard-title">VaultX — Encrypted Cloud Storage</h3>
        <p class="wcard-desc">
          Full-stack secure storage platform with searchable files, tamper-proof
          audit logs, and role-based access control. All encryption handled
          internally — no external key managers, no third-party crypto services.
          Built with FastAPI, Next.js, and PostgreSQL.
        </p>
        <div class="wcard-tags">
          <span class="wcard-tag">FastAPI</span><span class="wcard-tag"
            >Next.js</span
          ><span class="wcard-tag">PostgreSQL</span><span class="wcard-tag"
            >Docker</span
          ><span class="wcard-tag">Security</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/projects" class="wcard">
        <span class="wcard-arrow">↗</span>
        <div class="wcard-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="wcard-title">pico — Color Picker</h3>
        <p class="wcard-desc">
          Minimal X11 color picker built in Rust. Click anywhere, get the hex.
          Published on AUR.
        </p>
        <div class="wcard-tags">
          <span class="wcard-tag">Rust</span><span class="wcard-tag">X11</span
          ><span class="wcard-tag">AUR</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/projects" class="wcard">
        <span class="wcard-arrow">↗</span>
        <div class="wcard-num">03</div>
        <h3 class="wcard-title">DWM Dots</h3>
        <p class="wcard-desc">
          Riced Arch Linux setup — DWM patched from source, suckless toolset,
          every pixel intentional.
        </p>
        <div class="wcard-tags">
          <span class="wcard-tag">C</span><span class="wcard-tag">DWM</span
          ><span class="wcard-tag">Arch</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/projects" class="wcard">
        <span class="wcard-arrow">↗</span>
        <div class="wcard-num">04</div>
        <h3 class="wcard-title">Urja N Sonpal</h3>
        <p class="wcard-desc">
          E-Commerce for a brand — self-hosted on VPS, Nginx, PocketBase CMS.
          Built for real traffic.
        </p>
        <div class="wcard-tags">
          <span class="wcard-tag">Next.js</span><span class="wcard-tag"
            >Nginx</span
          ><span class="wcard-tag">VPS</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/projects" class="wcard">
        <span class="wcard-arrow">↗</span>
        <div class="wcard-num">05</div>
        <h3 class="wcard-title">Auto-Selfie</h3>
        <p class="wcard-desc">
          AI smile detection that auto-fires the camera. OpenCV + Haar cascades.
          Hands-free.
        </p>
        <div class="wcard-tags">
          <span class="wcard-tag">Python</span><span class="wcard-tag"
            >OpenCV</span
          ><span class="wcard-tag">ML</span>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <div class="process-strip">
    <div class="section-tag">03 — How I Work</div>
    <h2 class="section-h">The Process.</h2>
    <div class="process-grid">
      <div class="proc-item">
        <div class="proc-step">01</div>
        <div class="proc-title">Understand the problem</div>
        <div class="proc-desc">
          Before touching code — what are we actually building, why does it
          exist, and who uses it?
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="proc-item">
        <div class="proc-step">02</div>
        <div class="proc-title">Architecture first</div>
        <div class="proc-desc">
          DB schema, API contracts, deployment shape — decisions made upfront
          save weeks later.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="proc-item">
        <div class="proc-step">03</div>
        <div class="proc-title">Ship and iterate</div>
        <div class="proc-desc">
          Working software in front of real users fast. Optimize when you have
          data, not assumptions.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="proc-item">
        <div class="proc-step">04</div>
        <div class="proc-title">Own the stack</div>
        <div class="proc-desc">
          Self-host where it makes sense. Understand every layer. No mystery
          dependencies in prod.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CURRENTLY -->
  <div class="currently-strip">
    <div>
      <div class="section-tag">04 — Right Now</div>
      <h2 class="section-h">
        What I'm<br /><span style="color:var(--red)">up to.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="section-sub" style="margin-top:16px;">
        Real-time status — what's occupying my brain and hands this month.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="currently-items">
      <div class="curr-item">
        <span class="curr-badge">Learning</span>
        <p class="curr-text">
          <strong>Linux kernel internals</strong> — understanding syscalls, memory
          management, the scheduler. Going deeper than userspace.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="curr-item">
        <span class="curr-badge">Building</span>
        <p class="curr-text">
          <strong>Self-hosting stack</strong> — Nginx, Docker Compose, Cloudflare
          tunnels. Own your infra, own your data.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="curr-item">
        <span class="curr-badge">Exploring</span>
        <p class="curr-text">
          <strong>Kubernetes in production</strong> — moving beyond docker-compose
          for multi-service deployments on VPS.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="curr-item">
        <span class="curr-badge">Open To</span>
        <p class="curr-text">
          <strong>Freelance & full-time</strong> — full-stack roles, interesting problems,
          people who self-host their own stuff.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- GALLERY PEEK -->
  <div class="gallery-peek">
    <div class="gallery-peek-header">
      <div>
        <div class="section-tag">05 — Life</div>
        <h2 class="section-h">
